rvice Star Global War on Terrorism Expeditionary Medal Non Article 5 NATO  ISAF  Medal Global War on Terrorism Service Medal Iraq Campaign Medal w  2 Campaign Stars Army Service Ribbon Overseas Service Ribbon  3rd Award  Armed Forces Reserve Medal w  M Device  3rd Award  Joint Meritorious Unit award Combat Action Badge German Marksmanship Badge  Silver  Drill Sergeant Badge SSG Chip Lilly is a native of Staunton  VA  He enlisted into the Army Reserves in 1998 shortly after receiving his BA in Education from Berea College  He attended OSUT at Ft Knox as 19D Cavalry Scout  In 2002  he graduated from Drill Sergeant School  In 2004  he attended Combat Leaders Course at Ft Benning  GA  In 2005 2006  was deployed to Iraq as a MTT  and  2007 2008 was deployed to Afghanistan to serve as a Soldier Training Kandak  STK  Team Leader  In 2009  SSG Lilly was transitioned to 11B Infantryman  He has completed Infantryman Advanced Leader Course and first phase of Senior Leader Course  In 2012 20013  he was deployed as an Instructor for the Facility Security Forces  FSF  Kingdom of Saudi Arabia  He has been a Military Science instructor at Marist College  Fordham University and at Liberty University  University of Virginia  He is currently serving as a Senior Drill and Platoon SGT C Company 2 317 98th DIV  SSG Lilly is married and has three children and a grandson  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 